  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves multiple components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. Domestic Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Report (SAR) regulations\n\n3. Key Legal Elements\n- Criminal penalties for money laundering\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture provisions\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n- Financial institution compliance requirements\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Financial crimes investigations\n- Cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n- International information sharing\n- Prosecution of financial crimes\n\n5. Regulatory Bodies\n- Financial Crime Enforcement Network (FinCEN)\n- Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC)\n- Internal Revenue Service (IRS)\n- Department of Justice (DOJ)\n\n6. Compliance Obligations\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Risk assessment procedures\n- Internal control systems\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes.",
